title: [Quinton Manse, Hedged Garden]
description: Raspberry, carmine, and scarlet grow in profusion from the purple beech hedges the small garden, the red hues mingling with the nearly black purple leaves and dominating their hunter green cousins.  Tiled pavers arranged in odd angles create an elegant patio of alternating angles and dark hues.  Open for the moment, a glass-paned golden linden door offers access to the manse.
